            "page": "Film_Fire_Nation"
          }
        }
      ],
      "text": "The earthbending father was one of the prisoners in his village who was reunited with his son after Katara saved him from Fire Nation soldiers."
    },
    {
      "body": "His village was attacked by the Fire Nation before the beginning of the film. He and the other ${link_0} managed to defeat the invaders at first, but they were powerless when the Fire Nation came back with their war machines. As a term of surrender, the nonbenders of the village were allowed to live in peace, if the earthbenders were imprisoned and earthbending forbidden. Their earthbending-related tools were also confiscated. His son was later captured with ${link_1}, and they were reunited in the prison camp.",
      "links": [
        {
          "body": "earthbenders",
          "key": "${link_0}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Earthbending",
            "page": "Earthbending"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "Team Avatar",
          "key": "${link_1}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Team_Avatar",
            "page": "Team_Avatar"
          }
        }
      ],
      "text": "His village was attacked by the Fire Nation before the beginning of the film. He and the other earthbenders managed to defeat the invaders at first, but they were powerless when the Fire Nation came back with their war machines. As a term of surrender, the nonbenders of the village were allowed to live in peace, if the earthbenders were imprisoned and earthbending forbidden. Their earthbending-related tools were also confiscated. His son was later captured with Team Avatar, and they were reunited in the prison camp."
    },
    {
      "body": "Upon inquiry, he explained the situation to ${link_0}. When his son threw a pebble at the lead soldier, he earth-blocked a retaliatory fire attack, even though it was not acceptable for any prisoner to do so. He held his son close, waiting to be finished off by a combined attack from two ${link_1} when they were protected by a large earth-barrier, raised by six earthbenders bending in unison.",
      "links": [
        {
          "body": "Aang",
          "key": "${link_0}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Film_Aang",
            "page": "Film_Aang"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "firebenders",
          "key": "${link_1}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Firebending",
            "page": "Firebending"
          }
        }
      ],
      "text": "Upon inquiry, he explained the situation to Aang. When his son threw a pebble at the lead soldier, he earth-blocked a retaliatory fire attack, even though it was not acceptable for any prisoner to do so. He held his son close, waiting to be finished off by a combined attack from two firebenders when they were protected by a large earth-barrier, raised by six earthbenders bending in unison."
    }
